𝟲 𝗧𝗶𝗽𝘀 𝘁𝗼 𝗠𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝗔𝘇𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗗𝗲𝘃𝗢𝗽𝘀...📌

Whether you're a pro or just starting out, here are 6 tips to help you get the most out of Azure DevOps 👀 

1️⃣ 𝐋𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐠𝐞 𝐘𝐀𝐌𝐋 𝐏𝐢𝐩𝐞𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐞𝐬:
Ditch the classic UI-based pipelines and switch to YAML. It’s version-controlled, portable, and lets you manage your workflows as code, which is great for handling more complex setups.

2️⃣ 𝐇𝐚𝐧𝐝𝐥𝐞 𝐒𝐞𝐜𝐫𝐞𝐭𝐬 𝐋𝐢𝐤𝐞 𝐚 𝐏𝐫𝐨:
Use Variable Groups to store and reuse settings and credentials across your pipelines. For sensitive info, integrate Azure Key Vault. It’s a secure way to manage secrets and keeps things safe and tidy, simplifying secret management.

3️⃣ 𝐒𝐞𝐭 𝐔𝐩 𝐐𝐮𝐚𝐥𝐢𝐭𝐲 𝐆𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐬:
Enforce code standards before merging by setting up quality gates. Tools like SonarCloud or built-in tests can help with code coverage, linting, and static analysis. It keeps your codebase clean and reliable.

4️⃣ 𝐔𝐬𝐞 𝐑𝐞𝐥𝐞𝐚𝐬𝐞 𝐆𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐬 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐃𝐞𝐩𝐥𝐨𝐲𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬:
Automate your deployments with release gates. They let you set conditions that need to be met before the code moves to the next stage, giving you an extra layer of control and safety.

5️⃣ 𝐀𝐮𝐭𝐨𝐦𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐈𝐧𝐟𝐫𝐚𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐮𝐜𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐓𝐞𝐫𝐫𝐚𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐀𝐳𝐮𝐫𝐞 𝐏𝐢𝐩𝐞𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐞𝐬:
Combine Azure Pipelines with Terraform to automate your infrastructure deployments. Treat your infrastructure as code to ensure everything’s consistent and reliable across environments.

6️⃣ 𝐊𝐞𝐞𝐩 𝐚𝐧 𝐄𝐲𝐞 𝐨𝐧 𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐬 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐀𝐳𝐮𝐫𝐞 𝐌𝐨𝐧𝐢𝐭𝐨𝐫:
Integrate Azure Monitor and Application Insights with your pipelines to keep tabs on your app’s performance. This way, you can spot issues before they affect your users, keeping everything running smoothly.

Hope you found this useful! 💡 
